DIV1.P:
BON TON;
OR,
High Life above Stairs.

DIV1.HEAD:
BON TON;
OR,
High Life above Stairs.

SP.P:
Be a good lad, and I won't be worse than my word;
there's money for you—(gives him some,) but come strait
home, for I shall want to go to bed:

Stay, stay, my Lord, I wou'd not meet him now
for the world; if he sees me here alone with you,
he'll rave like a madman; put me up the chimney;
any where.

Nay, rather than you should be miserable, Colonel, I
will indulge your martial spirit; meet me in the field;
there's my gauntlet.

I reverence you, Sir, as a relation to that Lady, but
as her slanderer I detest you: her tears must be dried,
and my honour satisfied; you know what I mean;
take your choice;—time, place, sword or pistol;
consider it calmly, and determine as you please; I am
 soldier, Sir John.
